cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about adapting object detectors to different domains, which is a common problem in computer vision. The paper proposes a new method called Conditional Domain Normalization (CDN) to address this problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as disentangling domain-specific attributes and conditional normalization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the adaptation of object detectors in the context of robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper could also be relevant to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) since it deals with adapting models to different domains, which is a common problem in AI.
